detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value: This is a first course on numerical optimization and is aimed at senior undergraduates and junior graduate students. Students will learn how to solve engineering problems in design optimization, trajectory optimization, and data fitting.Topics include:Setting up and manipulating optimization problems, optimality conditions, numerical algorithms and software, nonlinear programming, sequential quadratic programming, gradient descent.
